                        "content": "The nurse is volunteering with an outreach program to provide basic health care for homeless people. Which finding, if noted, must be addressed first?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "80db17ea97ed8fdcd1b6b9666390fca1",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Applying 应用",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nThe nurse needs to address the complaints of pain and numbness and tingling in both feet first with this population. If the client perceives value to the service provided and the complaint is addressed, the client will be more likely to return for follow-up care. While the blood pressure, blood glucose, and vision results need follow-up, the client's stated concern must be addressed first.\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nNote the subject, the finding to be addressed, and focus on the strategic word, first. Recalling that adherence is a problem for this population will direct you to the correct option. Also note that the correct option is the only subjective finding.",
