                        "content": "The nurse is caring for a client in the emergency department who states they are homeless. Which statement, if made by the nurse, requires the need for further teaching?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "a0f7d178f7b728b8bba7ef20ddeca62d",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Evaluating 评价",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nIndividuals affected by homelessness are at increased risk for death related to chronic illness, environmental exposures, communicable diseases, mental illnesses, and many other conditions. Homeless individuals can also experience violence, and physical and emotional trauma. There are many reasons leading to homelessness, and disability is one factor but not necessarily the primary factor.\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nNote the strategic words, need for further teaching. These words indicate a negative event query and the need to focus on the option that is incorrect. Think about the characteristics of the homeless population; noting the word primarily in option 4 will direct you to this option.",
                        "id": "d932b09c20bb49a3991b9d618c7408c6",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "1"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
