                        "content": "A homeless parent brings their 1-year-old child to an emergency clinic. The nurse caring for this child understands that children affected by homelessness are most at risk for which problems? Select all that apply.",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "11797937e327eb6d913faa80427c566b",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nHomeless children will often be victims of malnourishment, leading to anemia, and while they may be diabetic, being homeless does not put them at greater risk for having diabetes. Typically, homeless children are underweight, not obese. Environmental exposures increase their risk of being asthmatics or getting ear infections. This pediatric population is sick more often and will have an increased incidence of mental health and behavioral problems.\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nNote the strategic word, most, to help guide your answer. Thinking about what health disparities affect the pediatric population without adequate access to shelter, food, or a primary health care provider will direct you to the correct options.",
                        "id": "5b35be7f1b6643aeac9680fa878a4c30",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "9f7ddca8629d4657befd6dd11008438c",
                                "content": "Focusing on reported symptoms"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "c3177944e99c4477bac98395325f0b24",
                                "content": "Being nonjudgmental and nonthreatening"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "92f107d39e25420bbb2b74a264718343",
                                "content": "Setting a follow-up appointment for the client"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "c0b514c803d842e4b8a85228f0c5287f",
                                "content": "Focusing on the obvious health abnormalities"
